<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="140" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="140">
Males of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. platensis" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="species" species="platensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">P. platensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished by the narrow distal arm of sternum IX with scattered lateral setae and by the posterior margin of sternum VIII which presents a right angle. Females have the ventral margin of bulga of spermatheca markedly indented (
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, FGAM" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" refId="B33" refString="Smit, FGAM, 1987. An illustrated catalogue of the Rothschild fleas (Siphonaptera) in the British Museum (Natural History) 7: Malacopsylloidea (Malacopsyllidae and Rhopalopsyllidae). Oxford University Press, Oxford" title="An illustrated catalogue of the Rothschild fleas (Siphonaptera) in the British Museum (Natural History) 7: Malacopsylloidea (Malacopsyllidae and Rhopalopsyllidae)." year="1987">Smit 1987</bibRefCitation>
); however, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lareschi, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" pagination="35 - 42" refId="B21" refString="Lareschi, M, Linardi, PM, 2009. Morphological variability in Polygenis (Polygenis) platensis (Jordan and Rothschild) (Siphonaptera: Rhopalopsyllidae: Rhopalopsyllinae) and taxonomic consequences. Zootaxa 2310: 35 - 42" title="Morphological variability in Polygenis (Polygenis) platensis (Jordan and Rothschild) (Siphonaptera: Rhopalopsyllidae: Rhopalopsyllinae) and taxonomic consequences." volume="2310" year="2009">Lareschi and Linardi (2009)</bibRefCitation>
observed a variation on this character and they reported that spermatheca can be indented or not. With respect to the record from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Guayapa”">&quot;Guayapa&quot;</normalizedToken>
, we found that the coordinates given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, FGAM" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" refId="B33" refString="Smit, FGAM, 1987. An illustrated catalogue of the Rothschild fleas (Siphonaptera) in the British Museum (Natural History) 7: Malacopsylloidea (Malacopsyllidae and Rhopalopsyllidae). Oxford University Press, Oxford" title="An illustrated catalogue of the Rothschild fleas (Siphonaptera) in the British Museum (Natural History) 7: Malacopsylloidea (Malacopsyllidae and Rhopalopsyllidae)." year="1987">Smit (1987)</bibRefCitation>
place the collecting locality at &quot;app. 3 km N of El Milagro, General Ocampo Department&quot;. The locality 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Guayapa”">&quot;Guayapa&quot;</normalizedToken>
in La Rioja Province is located at 
<geoCoordinate degrees="29" direction="south" minutes="51" orientation="latitude" precision="1" seconds="41.18" value="-29.861439">29°51'41.18&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="67" direction="west" minutes="14" orientation="longitude" precision="1" seconds="22.99" value="-67.239716">67°14'22.99&quot;W</geoCoordinate>
, which is about 180 km SE of the previous coordinates. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopez Berrizbeitia, MF" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la asociacion parasitologica Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" pagination="40 - 44" refId="B23" refString="Lopez Berrizbeitia, MF, Sanchez, RT, Diaz, MM, Lareschi, M, 2013. Los ectoparasitos de La Rioja: resultados preliminares. Revista de la asociacion parasitologica Argentina 1: 40 - 44" title="Los ectoparasitos de La Rioja: resultados preliminares." volume="1" year="2013">
<normalizedToken originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
Berrizbeitia et al. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
cited the host as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Akodon simulator" order="Siphonaptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulator">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Akodon simulator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we now use the name 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. glaucinus" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="species" species="glaucinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">A. glaucinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
following 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zsc.12014" author="Coyner, BS" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" pagination="335 - 350" refId="B8" refString="Coyner, BS, Braun, JK, Mares, MA, Van Den Bussche, RA, 2013. Taxonomic validity of species groups in the genus Akodon (Rodentia, Cricetidae). Zoologica Scripta 42: 335 - 350, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zsc.12014" title="Taxonomic validity of species groups in the genus Akodon (Rodentia, Cricetidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zsc.12014" volume="42" year="2013">Coyner et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. The collection from Ulapes from 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. chacoensis" order="Rodentia" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chacoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">G. chacoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
constitutes a new flea-host association, this result was expected, because 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. (P.) platensis" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" rank="species" species="platensis" subGenus="P.">P. (P.) platensis</taxonomicName>
has been recorded on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Graomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Graomys griseoflavus" order="Rodentia" pageId="1" pageNumber="140" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseoflavus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="140">Graomys griseoflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4103.3.3" author="Lareschi, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" pagination="239 - 258" refId="B22" refString="Lareschi, M, Sanchez, JP, Autino, AG, 2016. A review of the fleas (Insecta: Siphonaptera) from Argentina. Zootaxa 4103: 239 - 258, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4103.3.3" title="A review of the fleas (Insecta: Siphonaptera) from Argentina." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4103.3.3" volume="4103" year="2016">Lareschi et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The localities recorded are from the Dry Chaco and Monte Desert of Mountains and Isolated Valleys eco-regions.
</paragraph>
